title: S. W. Green to Walt Whitman, 3 May 1876
text: S. W. GREEN,Printer, Stereotyper, Electrotyper, and Binder,OFFICE, 18 JACOB STREET, CORNER FRANKFORT,New-York,3 May,1876May 3, 1876Walt Whitman, Esq431 Stevens St. CamdenN. J.New JerseyDear Sir:I have your letter of yesterday, and the "Leaves of Grass" with corrections. The making of the corrections, Paper like the sample indeed, and printing of 600 copies, 348 pages, will come to $157. If I have an order to that effect from you day after tomorrow morning, I will have the 600 copies ready for the Binder, as you ask, three weeks from to-day, 24 May, in unfolded sheets.I am also ready to bind them as you may direct, and will give figures if you indicate the styleYours trulyS.W. Green S. W. Green to Walt Whitman, 3 May 1876
